{"id":14881278,"mediaExerciseId":"da6e467c-2865-45a2-afdf-3b9240592dea","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"10","chapterTitle":"Making Capital Investment Decisions","groupId":612344,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":349,"solutions":[{"id":6310024,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will solve for the internal rate of return for the project. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The internal rate of return refers to the computation of the percentage return of the project that will make the net present value equal to zero. \n\nThis can be solved using this formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n0&=\\sum \\dfrac{\\text{net cash inflow}}{(1+\\text{internal rate of return})^\\text{time}}-\\text{Initial investment}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Another method to solve for this is by entering the cash flow and the initial investment in a spreadsheet. Once the values have been entered, type in $=\\text{IRR}(\\text{range of cells containing the values})$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"After doing the process, you will end up with the table of values and the internal rate of return:\n[![IRR.jpg](https://i.postimg.cc/4xY7FrTm/IRR.jpg)](https://postimg.cc/5XM2XKyV)\n\nThe internal rate of return for the project is $34\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"18ad30ea-50ca-419e-8896-5f64794b22af","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradfo